Day 13

        Review
        Single if : for one condition
            if(condition){
              Statement A
            }

        if & else : where there are two options / conditions/ possibilities (not more than 3 not lessthan 2 conditions)

            if(Condition){
            Statement A;
            Statement B;
           }else {
           Statement C;
           Statement D;
           }

           Statement A, B : if condition is true
           Statement C, d : if condition is false

           if()
           statementA;
           else
           statementB;

           Multi-Branch if: when there are three or more options

           if(condition1){
           Statement A;
           } else if(condition2){
           Statement B;
           } else {
            Statement C
           }

           Only one Block gets executed.

           Statement A: Condition1 must be True
           Statment  B: Condition1 Must be false, Condition2 Must be True
           Statement C: Condition1 & Condition2 Must be false

           Ternary Operator: (condition) ? (return if true) :(return if false);
           //                  num%2==0  ? "Cift Sayi"  : "Tek Sayi"
                             (condition) ? (return if true)  : (Ternary)

           Switch Statement : switch, case, break, default

           syntax:
            switch(Data){

              case data1:
                   Statements;
                  break;
              case data2:
                      Statements;
                      break;

              default :
                      Statements;

            }

        Case value Must match with Switch data type and Unique
        Switch Data can not be Long float double boolean data types
        break: used for exiting the switch
               if we dont use break statement, switch statment cont to execute the blocks until next break
        default: block get executed if none of the case matches

        For Loop

            Java for loop is used to run a block of code for a certain number of times. The syntax of for loop is:

            for (initialization; conditional; increment/decrement) {
                // body of the loop
                }

            The initialExpression initializes and/or declares variables and executes only once.
            The condition is evaluated. If the condition is true, the body of the for loop is executed.
            The updateExpression updates the value of initialExpression.
            The condition is evaluated again. The process continues until the condition is false.

        Odevler: Nested For loopa kadar yapilan yapilmayan tum Tasklar kendiniz hic birseye bakmadan yazmaya calisin!
               : If Tasks for Control Flow Statements Hafta sonuna kadar yapin;


